      "writtenOn": "2020-12-02T00:02:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I understand treating the zero value specially can be error prone. However I also feel it a bit strange that every caller should fill a field which is just for unit tests.\nAnother point is as you said there are a lot of unit tests that need be updated. I think forgetting to update a test means specifying zero to CustomGracePeriod is also error-prone.\n\nHow about making the type of CustomGracePeriod *time.Duration ?",
